Articles.Content: Hi, so I have a modded install that I use for my career mode saves and I recently updated this to KSP 1.2 as all the mods I use have been updated. However, when I attempted to load the game for the first time in 1.2, not only were none of my games displayed under the resume saved tab, but when I closed that tab, I could not reopen it. I thought that this was a corrupted save, not a big deal since I had a recent backup, but not only did replacing the save with the backup not work, but when I reverted to 1.1.3 again, it worked fine along with all mods. Stranger still is that other saves, including ones created in 1.1.3 worked on 1.2 if the non-functional save was removed from the saves folder. I am utterly baffled by this and despite my numerous efforts, including attempting to manually update the persistent for my career save, I have been unable to resolve the issue. I would really appreciate any input since I really want to play in 1.2.

I've had this exact same problem.

 

I had 1.2 working for a week or two.

All of a sudden, none of my saves were in the load selection. Then, i couldn't re-open the save selection menu.

I went into the KSP saves file folder, my saves were all there.

I though a mod did something.

 

I deleted ALL local game content (except my saves), did a re-install, no mods, created a game, saved it, quit and restarted, not there, same menu bug.

 

Obviously not a problem with mods, as the second time there were none.

This needs to be patched real soon.
